  "name": "Morrison COU1 — CPB hemolysis credibility assessment (High Assurance)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under cardiopulmonary bypass (CPB) conditions. COU1 evaluates whether the computational model can identify worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for a Class II CPB device at Model Risk Level 2. Full 13-factor assessment: 7 factors assessed (all meeting required levels), 6 factors not assessed (acceptable at MRL 2). Assurance level is declared High, reflecting the comprehensive verification and validation campaign conducted across multiple operating points. All credibility factors meet or exceed required gradations under MRL 2 requirements.",
